<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06241020 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06241020 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  STOCK; INVESTMENT; COMPANY; FINANCE; LOAN; RANKING; DECREASE; FRAUD  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Moody's Investors Service Inc. today lowered the credit rating of billions ofdollars in Salomon Inc. debt because of the bond-trading scandal engulfing theWall Street firm.;   The action by the rating agency is expected to increasethe costs Salomon will have to bear in borrowing money to run its businesses,but Moody's said Salomon's capital base was not at risk.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Business  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  MOODY'S CUTS SALOMON'S CREDIT RATING  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     Moody's downgraded about $7 billion in long-term debt issued by Salomon, aswell as more than $6 billion in commercial paper, which are short-term IOUsthat Wall Street firms issue regularly to finance daily operations.;   Thecredit-rating agency said it lowered the credit rating on Salomon's seniordebt to A3 from A2, and reduced its rating on commercial paper to Prime-2 fromthe highest level, Prime-1. All of Salomon's debt, however, remains at aninvestment-grade status.;   Moody's said it would continue reviewing Salomon'sdebt. &quot;Of particular concern&quot; it said, &quot;will be the nature of any criminalcharges that may be brought against the firm, as well as the various judicialand regulatory sanctions that may be imposed.&quot;  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Associated Press  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  New York  </CITY><EDITION>  Stock Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910828  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Wednesday  </DAY><MONTH>  August  </MONTH><PG.COL>  15E  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  185  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Wednesday, August 28, 199100241020,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>